snippet: The Labor Party’s youth camp is reopening Friday for the first time since a right-wing extremist gunned down 69 people there four years ago.
abstract: Youth camp run by Norway's Labor Party on island of Utoya reopens for first time since 2012 shooting rampage by right-wing extremist Anders Behring Breivik that killed 69 people.
lead_paragraph: The Labor Party’s youth camp is reopening Friday for the first time since a right-wing extremist gunned down 69 people there four years ago.

headline.main: Norway: Party’s Youth Camp to Reopen at Island Site of 2011 Massacre
headline.print_headline: Europe; Norway: Party’s Youth Camp to Reopen at Island Site of Massacre in 2011
